WeatherInfluence contains contains methods for returning the amount (in percentage) of the image that is obstructed from view by weather effects based on weather parameters.

HydrometeorDetection is an uncompleted version of the code described in the paper "Rain or Snow Detection in Image Sequences
Through Use of a Histogram of Orientation Streaks" [Bossu et. al] The end goal was to provide a direct mapping of rain pixels from real images into affected detection ranges.
